fields.name: Chateau Bois Pertuis
fields.description: The first bottle added to FromVin. This rich, delicate blend has a place in our heart. Medium to full bodies, bursting with flavours of Blackcurrant.

fields.name: Estepa Reserve Merlot
fields.description: Thirst quenching and delectable, this wine can take most of your flavorsome foods and enhance them. Oaky in flavour and medium in body, don't miss out on this one.

fields.name: La Grande Allee Bordeaux
fields.description: Heavier than a traditional Bordeaux, the dark fruit aroma will draw you in and the velvet flavour will warm you through.

fields.name: Santa Carolina Coupage
fields.description: Well structured and balanced, this Tinto from the heights of Chile can handle a hearty beef dish or the strongest of cheeses.

fields.name: Penfolds Kalimna
fields.description: Mineral and Oak abound in this lively blend from Southern Australia. New world wine in an old world style and a wonderful addition to a varied selection.

fields.name: Nuits Saint Georges
fields.description: Predominantly made from Pinot Noir, this blend is one of our more distinguished offerings. Named for the patron Saint George, this wine is sturdy in character and holds notes of dark fruits and liquorice. For the collectors, this is also one that grows deeper and stronger with age.

fields.name: Penfolds Grande Hermitage
fields.description: An excellent mature wine, this Australian star should draw novice and connoisseur enthusiasts alike. A blend of Shiraz and Cabernet Sauvignon, this wine will match a medium to strong cheese with wonderful results.

fields.name: Portalegre Alentejo
fields.description: From right on the border between Portugal and Spain, this Portalegre offering is rich and spicy to taste. For a wine that you'll continue tasting long after it's gone, pick this one.

fields.name: Smith and Hook
fields.description: French, Oaked and derived from Cabernet Sauivgnon grapes, your senses will be met with Plum, Cherry and Vanilla tones. Great with a variety of foods, this one can be classed as easy drinking and is readily consumed on it's own also.

fields.name: Swartland Pinotage
fields.description: A FromVin favourite. This Pinotage is somehow bursting with red berries and plums, yet also offers early tones and aftertastes. We can't recommend this one enough.

fields.name: Thalia Syrah
fields.description: This Syrah is delectably soft with earth and spice notes. Stemming from Crete, we agree when this wine is described as a refreshing time by the locals who created it.

fields.name: Werken Syrah
fields.description: A delightful Chilean Syrah. Pair this with a lighter dish to enhance the experience all round.

fields.name: Moschofilero Boutari
fields.description: We're pleased to present this selection from one of the top wineries in Greece. You'll be pleasantly greeted by citrus notes, along with white rose and orange blossom aromas.

fields.name: Granger Bay Sauvignon Blanc
fields.description: Originating in the Western Cape of South Africa, we give this one a crisp, punchy rating with the overriding flavour of tart grapefruit.

fields.name: Leopard's Leap
fields.description: If you're looking for a pleasing Chardonnay, look no further. None of the oak, all of a delightful combination of lime, buttery biscuit and punchy pear.

fields.name: Lugana
fields.description: Hailing from a tiny, almost unknown part of Italy this wine belies it's humble origins. Utilising the unique grape Turbiana, white stone fruit and a hint of almond is what will greet you when you crack this one open.

fields.name: Nobilo of New Zealand
fields.description: A wonderfully fruity sauvignon which will leaving you wanting more of it's mixture of pinapple, and passionfruit flavours. On the nose, you'll find it to have hints of herbals and elderflower.

fields.name: Lheraud Pineau Blanc
fields.description: Known for their cognac, Lheraud also make a wonderful bottle of wine. Deep in flavour and much fuller than your average white, this smooth offering will leave you craving just another glass.
